Hormone replacement therapy may slow the ageing process in middle-aged women susceptible to Alzheimer’s disease.

A new study found healthy menopausal women who carried a well-known genetic risk factor for Alzheimer’s did not experience a decline when they took HRT.

The gene variant, known as ApoE4, has been shown to accelerate biological ageing.

